# TradeFrame — Privacy Policy

**Effective Date:** March 16, 2026
**Last Updated:** March 16, 2026

Twelve52 LLC ("we," "us," or "our") built TradeFrame as a commercial application. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the TradeFrame iOS application ("App").

---

## Information We Collect

### Information You Provide

- **Business Information** — Company name, phone number, and email address entered in Settings. This information is stored locally on your device and used solely to populate your PDF reports, estimates, and invoices.

- **Client Information** — Names, addresses, phone numbers, and email addresses of your clients. This data is entered by you and stored locally to manage your client relationships within the App.

- **Job, Estimate, Invoice, and Payment Data** — Job details, line items, financial amounts, payment records, milestones, and notes you create while using the App. All of this data is entered by you and stored locally on your device.

- **Signatures** — When you capture a customer signature (drawn on-screen or photographed), the image is stored with the associated estimate or report on your device.

### Information Collected Automatically

- **Photos and Camera** — When you use TradeFrame's camera to document jobs, photos are captured and stored within the App's local data store. Photos are never uploaded to our servers.

- **Location Data** — With your permission, TradeFrame accesses your device's GPS coordinates when you take a photo. These coordinates are embedded in the photo metadata and optionally displayed as a watermark. Location data is captured only at the moment of photo capture and is not tracked continuously. If you deny location access, the App functions normally but photos will not include GPS data.

- **Speech/Microphone** — With your permission, TradeFrame uses on-device speech recognition to transcribe voice notes when capturing photos. Audio is processed locally using Apple's Speech framework and is not transmitted to any external server. No audio recordings are stored — only the resulting text transcription.

- **Calendar** — With your permission, TradeFrame reads and writes events to your default Apple Calendar to sync job schedules. We do not access calendars beyond what is necessary to create and manage job events.

---

## How Your Data Is Stored

### Local Storage

All data you enter into TradeFrame — clients, jobs, photos, estimates, invoices, payments, milestones, and settings — is stored locally on your device using Apple's Core Data framework. We do not operate our own servers and do not collect or transmit your data to any server we control.

### iCloud Sync (CloudKit)

If you are signed into iCloud on your device, TradeFrame uses Apple's CloudKit to sync your data across your iOS devices. This means your data is stored in your personal iCloud account, managed and encrypted by Apple under their privacy policies. When iCloud is unavailable (or in the iOS Simulator), the App falls back to local-only storage.

We do not have access to your iCloud data. Synced data is governed by [Apple's Privacy Policy](https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/).

### Photo Storage

Photos taken through TradeFrame are stored in the App's local data directory (not your device's Photo Library) and synced via CloudKit if iCloud is enabled. We do not upload, access, or process your photos on any external server.

---

## How We Use Your Information

We use the information described above solely to:

- Display your business information on PDF reports, estimates, and invoices you generate
- Organize and present your client, job, and financial data within the App
- Embed GPS coordinates and timestamps in job photos for documentation purposes
- Transcribe voice notes to text for inclusion with photos and reports
- Sync your data across your devices via iCloud (if enabled)
- Schedule local notifications for job reminders, estimate/invoice nudges, and payment follow-ups
- Create calendar events for scheduled jobs

We do not use your data for advertising, profiling, marketing, or any purpose beyond operating the App for you.

